reviews.review_text: Microphone to FM This is a microphone recording of an FM broadcast--spot vbr file check shows a mono mix, occassionally boomy base, some patches/splices sub-par quality. Fans of the period may find it worthwhile.

Great Other One Sandwich Also like the ramble On Rose encore!
Peace, Bob
Wish I was there Not the best recording here on the Archive, but thank you for preserving this. Awesome setlist and lots of energy
Pretty sweet Other One, with Keith pianoing away very beautifully, but other than that a pretty average '71 show & slightly below-average recording.

Attention to sources This recording now makes me read the sources and lineage a lot more carefully!  I got all excited with that big bold SBD out front, then come to realize after a previous reviewer noted this is actually SBD broadcast over FM and taped with a microphone onto a cassette.  Not a great recording, which is doubly too bad for me because it is the first Wharf Rat in a few shows chronologically.
Entirely high energy show Jerry is on a roll for close to three hours.

My first show Thank you for sharing the music that started my journey on the bus! It was a magical night. I really enjoyed listening to it again. Magical night as it snowed while we were in the concert!

Picky On The Pickin' Despite Any Recording Glitches,Hiss Or Taping Lineage This One Should Be Appreciated A Bit More. From The Past Reviewers You Would Think This A Sub Par Show For The Period. I Find The Band Engaged Fully With Each Other And Their Surroundings. Jerry Seems A Bit More Animated Than Usual. Connecting With The Crowd And It Transfers Directly To His Playing. Grate Slow Blues Riffs In The First Section Of The Other One. Despite The Sound  Breaking Off A Bit After A Splice The Transition From Uncle And The Jam With Phil In The Reprise Make This One Special. So Much Negative Energy Coming From The Reviewers. Learn To Appreciate What You See, Hear And Feel. This One, Hearing The Band Enjoy Their Craft And Their Jaunt Through The Southwest, Makes Me FEEL GOOD.
My birthday show! I was born on this very day, so of course it's a great show!
First show My first Dead show, meet a chick at the show and was left in N.J. Was a great night.

Memories New Riders opened for them right?

The Dead played for hours!

Two Questions: Did Jerry play slide for the New Riders in the opening show ,Ike h3 did on their first album?

And

Was Pigpen still playing with the Dead then?

I can’t remember.

One of the best . . . This is one f the best GD shows I have ever heard. Far better than Austin 11/15/71 imho. I am content to listen to this version although I do have the ability to turn down the extra bass on my system. Does it get much better than good dead?!
